<br>
ive already done the dual wield,max thrust/cs stuff,max stealth etc. at level 43 life baen does 50 a tick,for 5-6 ticks,thats 300 points damage. if you want to use the debuff ,thats possible as well. with weapon swtiching,its possible to bs with debuff,and then switch and land lifebane.<br>
<br>
with the exception of tanks using a dot poison would be more useful on all other classes due to low health. given that 2h weapons are doing immense cs damage compard to 1h ,envenom seems to be a logical chioce.<br>
<br>
The only thing i might alter is drop sword down,dependant on the revamped cs style tree. if theres a high level normal attack at most times,as well as higher level cs styles,or higher envenom that i want,i mgiht drop sword to 25&lt;35 with skill bonus&gt; and use the points in other areas.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uthegulogulo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>the Gulo Gulo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.wlvrn.com/images/dag.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/7/01 4:11:28 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.wlvrn.com/images/bert.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Most RvR Lethal Sadowblade Spec?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> at level 43 life baen does 50 a tick,for 5-6 ticks,thats 300 points damage. if you want to use the debuff ,thats possible as well. with weapon swtiching,its possible to bs with debuff,and then switch and land lifebane.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->5-6 ticks is good only if:<br>
<br>
You're dead and you want him to die later.<br>
You're gunning for a long fight -- not good.<br>
<br>
The debuff drop in hitpoints is &gt; instant &lt; and therefore more desireable.  Especially (pretty sure here) because the debuff poison hits first, then your backstab lands (need a playing rogue to confirm, either way it's good) and he's dead.<br>
<br>
As for sword spec, I find that at higher levels, I basically only use Assault.  The only reason I crank my sword spec it so up my average damage output.  As a Skald, I'm in there for quite a bit sometimes and therefore it pays off.<br>
<br>
My suggestion Aiden, would be to lower your sword spec and put the points into Stealth.  Stealth is *really* important for Rogues as, along with making YOU harder to see, it makes it easier for you to see enemy archers who are stealthed.  Your level in critical strike is what I think the backstab is based off of, it then takes into account your weapon's damage and any bonuses... NOT the level of spec you have in that weapon.  I'm not sure, but that's what I would expect.  Again, would need a ShadowBlade who's currently playing to give some input in that.<br>
<br>
In my opinion, that's one of your greatest assests... you can find and kill archers; a class that's near impossible for any other class to find. <p><hr>
