<br>
i stated that the 5-6 tick poison would be used on tanks. most other classes were more suited to the instant debuff.<br>
<br>
an instant debuff on a tank really wont do much, irrreguardless 43 envenom will give you the highest level dot. and the 2nd highest level in all other poisons. either way will have options for it. unless the debuff lasts for 35-40 seconds,vs the dot. still the nice thing is you can use both if need be.<br>
<br>
as far as raising stealth. +skill items,still give you the appropriate level bonus vs exp level. the only thing you dont get is the styles from your spec line.  so at 35 stealth,its possible to get a total of 40 stealth from +skill items. with the new rvr bonus in how realm points improve skill,you can get up to 45 skill. the only unknown with that is if +skill items,and the rvr bonus stack,in which case you could get +15 skill ,thus max stealth.<br>
<br>
same thing applies with sword,there really isnt any reason to raise it up higher. except for use with styles. you can still get the appropriate damage bonus from skill items/rvr points. your weapon damage from skill works in tandom with cs damage,they are interdependant at this time.<br>
<br>
as far as rvr goes, right now,most everyone i encounter,outside of larger group situations, runs everytime you land a critical strike. since your dealing with lag,and other issues its a debate to let poison finish them off ,or try to kill them with the debuff poisons.<br>
<br>
At any rate,all of this is still conjecture,because when mythic finally completes the skill set for the rogues,everything everyone is doing right now,could be totally wrong.<br>
